# Enforce LF line endings on every text file, cross-platform. The Windows CI runner
# checked out `.tks`/`.tkt` as CRLF (git autocrlf), so `teko fmt`'s canonical-LF output
# read those files back as non-idempotent and the fmt corpus tests panicked (issue #229).
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` pins text files to LF on
# checkout regardless of platform, keeping the corpus byte-consistent everywhere.
* text=auto eol=lf
